@Zuul33: I'm pretty sure you're talking about [Mogg Maniac](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg Maniac), not [Mogg Fanatic](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg Fanatic).  

But yeah, using [en-Kor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=en-Kor) creatures with [Mogg Maniac](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mogg Maniac) - or preferably even [Spitemare](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spitemare) or [Stuffy Doll](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stuffy Doll) - to make use of this ridiculous drawback seems to be a good idea.  

Get your opponent to know how your creatures feel about a *Sorrow's Path* [Pyroclasm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroclasm), yay!
